CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1967, pg. 17, reads: "All Ears - Good looking Charlotte Nelson seems to be all ears as she listens to Ahmed Algazali of Nigeria, Africa, tell of some of the interesting customs of his country. This was taken as the AKA's "Ajoyo."
TitMainTitle: Ahmed Algazali wearing African style clothing, and Charlotte Nelson wearing contrasting curve patterned dress, in the Flying Carpet for Alpha Kappa Alpha's "Ajoyo"
